Text.Value: About that creature in the cage...
Nur. Sery. Here. They become.

EditorData.NodeContext: Vacant; a decent pause between each word

Text.Value: Down. Deep. One of Three. One of Three.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: This is the only moment where he becomes almost lucid/emotive
EditorData.NodeContext: Breathlessly/suddenly audibly fearful, almost sobbing - before immediately returning to being monosyllabic once this line is over

Text.Value: Odd. Other. Beyond One Mind.
About the 'little kitty' in the cage...
Do as you will with it.
Leave.
*Or you could take advantage of its vulnerability and plunder what's left of its hollow mind for anything that could serve you.*
What is this place?
...Yes. Yes. Take - only One song remains.
No. No. Wrong song.
But there is one. Little. Kitty. Dances. To another song.
Why don't I send you to join all these creatures you butchered?
*With a lurch, you realise he means the intellect devourers. Here the brains are harvested - made part of the hivemind.*
A ghaik thrall. The only way to save it is to kill it.
Become what?
Mas. Ter? No.
Free the creature or I'll kill you and every one of your creations.
*You could kill it, end its miserable life of enslavement. Surely that would be the humane thing to do...*
Enter his thoughts.
*You focus on the source of the power, but it is quiet and still. It needs to rest.*
What's wrong with it?
No. No. Kitties good. Sing One song. Take other. Away!
Let it come with me. We sing the same song.
...Yes. Yes. I hear. Go then. Make. Happy?
No. NO. I CHOP!

EditorData.NodeContext: Confusion and denial building into rage - attacking after node

Text.Value: *Pliant as well-worn boots, his mind turns to his work. Chop. Cut. Sort.*
*No will sparks behind his eyes. His mind has been hollowed out, to better echo the commands of the collective.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: Could use an idle of the Butcher mindlessly chopping and sorting away. <LoganP>

Text.Value: I need to find your master - Ketheric.
What did you do to all these people?
Chop. Chop. Help them. Become?
Careful petting. Sticky.
Part of One Mind. Four little feet. Dancing. To same song.

EditorData.NodeContext: Vacant; a decent pause between each sentence

Text.Value: Cut. Chop. Until it is us again.
I'll take the creature with me. It won't disrupt the hivemind anymore.
*You focus on the source of the power, but it is quiet and still. It needs to rest.*
*Shiver of impact. Crack of bone. He removes the brains, digs free the squirming tadpoles. The unworthy ones, given over to the illithids. To become.*
Where can I find this 'Little Kitty'?
Yes. Yes. Please.
Kill? Cut? Chop?
Bad kitty. Sings wrong song. Must-fix.
Same. Song. As you?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Tilting his head at us in vacant confusion / interest

Text.Value: No. No. Must-fix. MUST-FIX!

EditorData.NodeContext: Confusion and denial building into rage - attacking after node

Text.Value: OTHER. WRONG SONG!

EditorData.NodeContext: Confusion and denial building into rage - attacking after node

Text.Value: Locked. Up. Bad kitty. Thinks it is. Other.
Let it come with me. We sing the same song.

Synopsis: This dialog is started by talking to the Butcher character in the Colony. The player may ask the Butcher questions or recruit them as a temporary follower inside the Colony. Alternatively, this dialog runs through a flag in case the player has already met the Butcher, or if the Butcher was recruited as a follower. The Butcher sounds eerily vacant unless otherwise specified, his mind destroyed by his time in Colony.
